{
  "text": "The examples discussed above, and specifically the relation [CITATION_1] , all support a lore in the community that generic black hole microstates must be formed by collapse processes on timescales much longer than M . In particular, one might conjecture that the relation (1) is generic, valid in order of magnitudes for all collapse scenarios. The purpose of this paper is to investigate this lore and see if there is any evidence against it.",
